  <summary date="2009-06-02T21:15:22Z" status="Introduced in House">Amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to require that a nonimmigrant foreign student seeking to enter the United States to study at a language training program enroll at a language program that is accredited by an accrediting agency recognized by the Secretary of Education.

Provides for a specified three-year exception to such requirement.</summary>
